Title: Series: Four landscapes with the Holy Family on their Flight into Egypt
Description: The Holy Family resting in front of a cave on the flight into Egypt. Mountainous landscape with Joseph reclining at centre next to the grazing ass, the Virgin attended to by two angels as she sits with the Christ Child at right; from a series of four plates Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Herman van Swanevelt
Curator's comments: This is one from a series of four, for comment see 1844,0425.15. This is second state, for another impression see S.2278; for first state of this plate, see S.2276.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (9.II)
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Sir Hans Sloane (with Philipe's oval blindstamp and initials HS)
